<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-23-0488 </DOCNO><TEXT>The role of computerized tomography (CT) in external beam radiotherapyregarding the diagnostic aspects of therapy planning and the therapyaspects including making accurate dosimetry calculations is briefly described.The application of CT in planning plesiotherapy (interstitial and intracavitarytechniques) is discussed in greater detail. This includes using CT forobtaining accurate three-dimensional anatomical information regardingtumour volume and surrounding structures and for localizing the geometryof sources after implantation for dose distribution calculations in multipleplanes. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>